EXTENDED OUTLOOK
SUNDAY TO WEDNESDAY
ISSUED BY THE MET OFFICE ON BEHALF OF THE COASTGUARD AND MARITIME AGENCY
AT 052300 UTC
SUNDAY EVENING A RIDGE OF HIGH PRESSURE FM THE AZORES HIGH WILL EXTEND
NE TO THE W OF THE BRITISH ISLES WITH A SHALLOW LOW 1004 CENTRED OVER DENMARK.
DURING MONDAY THE RIDGE IS EXP TO MOV SLWY E INTO THE BRITISH ISLES WITH
A SHALLOW LOW PERSISTING NEAR DENMARK AND WITH A FURTHER LOW MOV SLWY NE
TOWARDS ICELAND. SOME UNCERTAINTIES THEREAFTER BUT CURRENT EXPECTATIONS
ARE FOR THE RIDGE TO TRANSFER SE ACROSS THE UK ON TUESDAY AS THE SHALLOW
LOW NEAR ICELAND MOVS E TOWARDS SEA AREA FAEROES. THE LOW IS THEN CURRENTLY
FCST TO MOV SE ACROSS THE BRITISH ISLES ON WEDNESDAY. NO GALES ARE CURRENTLY
EXP FOR THE NITON FCST AREA THROUGH THIS PERIOD. HOWEVER WINDS MAY INCREASE
STRG ACROSS SEA AREAS SOLE FASTNET AND SHANNON BY LATE WEDNESDAY AFTERNOON
CONFIDENCE IS LOW AT THIS STAGE
